More boats were placed in our harbor along with much more larger trash on the shorelines like a cardboard box titled dock parts. There also were groups of baby fish and the red algae seem to be building up near the surface of the water. I also had to redo the titration because it was 4.6 and 5.2, then got this second round of results much closer.

properties.Name: Abigail Hils
properties.Site_Description: Offatts Bayou @ Sea Scouts Base Galveston
properties.Comments: Some foam and scum near the shoreline as the rest of our docks are being installed. Oppositely, the red algae has begun to grow outwards creating more habitat which allows for the plethora of juvenile fish all along the docks. Comb jellies were present too! Loads of red flakes appeared inside the bottle when beginning the D.O. tests. It will be interesting to compare before and after construction of the water quality as well as how long it will take for the algae to grow.

properties.Name: Abigail Hils
properties.Site_Description: Offatts Bayou @ Sea Scouts Base Galveston
properties.Comments: Some foam on the water and the wind was high. Yesterday the construction team cleaned their funnel for the dock poles in the water creating streams of grey sediments in the water. They cleaned it twice, once on the opposite side of the dock and then the second time it was cleaned right by my sample point. There is also loads of trash on the beaches since last Friday when a team cleaned it.

properties.Name: Abigail Hils
properties.Site_Description: Offatts Bayou @ Sea Scouts Base Galveston
properties.Comments: Some bubbles as usual, but the dockside near the lift machine very gross with yellow foam. Loads of baby mullet and quite a few larger adult mullet along the docks. Still need to learn the different algae on the docksides. Biggest scare is that I now see both (5) sea nettles (tentacles as long as my arm) and one moon jellies where my swimming area will be placed. I am in big trouble!! Need a net to protect the kids or loads of vinegar, petroleum jelly and credit cards. The water temperature is hotter than the air temperature, oh boy! Summer has arrived!

properties.Name: Abigail Hils
properties.Site_Description: Offatts Bayou @ Sea Scouts Base Galveston
properties.Comments: Huge storms passing through with heavy winds produced more trash in our wetlands and shoreline than I wanted. It also increased the oil slick on the water with a nice sheer effect that dissipates after a day or two. There also is scum near the shoreline and bubbles along the dock where the waves continually hit.

properties.Name: Abigail Hils
properties.Site_Description: Offatts Bayou @ Sea Scouts Base Galveston
properties.Comments: It has been a fantabulous two weeks of camp where no storms have passed through. We have quite a bit of algae that I scraped off at another spot and it took about five days for it to start again. There is no scum near my location but close to the shore there is a dead sheepshead fish and quite a bit of yellow foam. I also found a pipefish on my swim line behind my sample site. The biggest observation is the dredging located two docks down from me for the BaySmart, I want to sample the dirt please.

properties.Comments: The water is very flat today, not much wind and very few ripples. This allows for my sampling area to be clear enough to see the different algae stratification. No creatures found on or near the dockside, not even baby fish. The dredging is continuous and I want to still sample the sediments, but I have not taken the courage to sample it. 07/252 - 0 in, 07/21 - 0in, 07/20 - 0.8 in, 07/19 - 0.40 in

There is not much wake happening, everything is very calm. 08/06 - 0.28 in, 08/05 - 0 in, 08/04 - 0 in

properties.Name: Abigail Hils
properties.Site_Description: Offatts Bayou @ Sea Scouts Base Galveston
properties.Comments: There was a bit of foam on the surface around the docks where the waves/very strong ripples were hitting the docks. It made it difficult to see the secchi disk and I also got some of the foam in my bucket. But it dissipated once inside and there was no wind to influence it. It sprinkled this morning but apparently was trace amounts according to FWS precipitation totals. I accidentally put 9 drops of Manganese sulfate but it did not affect the titration. It also is interesting at how high my DO went up in the last month.

properties.Name: Abigail Hils
properties.Site_Description: Offatts Bayou @ Sea Scouts Base Galveston
properties.Comments: Some foam on the surface of the water, about the same amount that my site usually has from the ripples hitting the side of the docks. Interesting enough, the algae now has become a turf algae without any wavy red or green algae. It is funny looking and definitely different because it does not house the tiny crabs so I wonder what changed. Our low tides are rather high this week, to the point that our wetlands are full of water! It is exciting to see, but we do have bare spots to fill this next year. Maybe we can be a new site for the Marsh Mania to help plant our wetlands?!!!

properties.Name: Abigail Hils
properties.Site_Description: Offatts Bayou @ Sea Scouts Base Galveston
properties.Comments: I was doing water quality with two of our new interns (Emily and Nathan)! Both were super excited, though neither are biology focused high school students. As soon as we got there, a large sheepshead was drifting around one of the poles. We also saw loads of small ctenophores again and quite a few love bugs. There wasnt much in or out on the water. There were minimal bubbles/foam and no debris. It also was very calm and cool, though it was apparent this morning we had rain but nothing to influence runoff. The water also was murky due to the construction workers still going hard on finishing the waterfront and also from the wetlands. Also, the algae was very short again, so only common was my choice.
